27/08/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Anti-corruption prosecutors announced on Thursday (August 26th) they have pressed charges against three former senior officials at the national railway company, CFR, for alleged fraud worth 700,000 euros.
The three, including former CFR General-Manager Alexandru Noaptes, are charged with abuse of office affecting the public interest.
According to prosecutors, in 2005 the trio was involved in the purchase of second-hand equipment at inflated prices.
(AP, Gandul, Realitatea, Hotnews.ro - 26/08/10)
